autostart_locations.location: Task Scheduler\Mozilla\Zen Default Browser Agent F0DC299D809B9700

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a dropper/installer that establishes persistence through the Windows Task Scheduler. It checks for an "uninstall" command-line argument to remove a previously created task. Otherwise, it executes a file named "zen.exe" from its own directory, launching it as a detached process with the arguments "--backgroundtask defaultagent". This behavior, combined with the use of a deceptive description "Default Browser Agent" and COM-based task manipulation, is characteristic of malware setting up persistence on a victim machine.
